# Project Structure

The project is a Brutalist-style development environment with GitHub repository browsing functionality. The main components are:

- [coderx/src/main.tsx](mdc:coderx/src/main.tsx) - Entry point that renders the React application
- [coderx/src/App.tsx](mdc:coderx/src/App.tsx) - Main App component that provides the layout
- [coderx/src/components/RepoBrowser.tsx](mdc:coderx/src/components/RepoBrowser.tsx) - Core component for browsing GitHub repositories
- [coderx/src/components/FileViewer.tsx](mdc:coderx/src/components/FileViewer.tsx) - Component for viewing file contents
- [coderx/src/App.css](mdc:coderx/src/App.css) - Primary CSS styles for the application
- [coderx/src/index.css](mdc:coderx/src/index.css) - Global CSS styles including React Complex Tree overrides

The application allows users to:
1. Enter a GitHub repository URL
2. Fetch and display the repository's file tree
3. Navigate the file structure
4. View the contents of selected files
